 - A Statement is a basic unit of computation in a C++ program (Smallest thing in the program that the CPU can process

 - Every C++ program is a collection of statements organised in a certain way to achieve some goal

 - Statements end with a semicolon in C++ (;)

 - Statements are executed in order from top to bottom when the program is run
 
 - Execution keeps going until there is a statement causing the program to terminate, or 
	run another sequence of statements
